-- Shell Midstream files for US IPO
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Wed Jun 18, 2014 06:15AM EDT
-- None



June 18 (Reuters) - Shell Midstream Partners LP, a master limited partnership formed by Royal Dutch Shell Plc <RDSa.L>, filed with U.S. regulators on Wednesday to raise up to $750 million in an initial public offering of common units.

Barclays and Citigroup are underwriting the IPO, the Houston, Texas-based company said in a preliminary prospectus filed with the U.S Securities and Exchange Commission. (http://bit.ly/1iG7z6c)